**Secretary of State ANTONY BLINKEN,**  this morning: âWe have serious concerns that the result announced does not reflect the will or the votes of the Venezuelan people. â¦ The international community is watching this very closely and will respond accordingly.â
**A CRUCIAL THREE WEEKS â** The âsugar highâ is about to wear off.
**Yes, VP KAMALA HARRIS** has had a . Yes, she has managed to reset Democratsâ chances against GOP nominee **DONALD TRUMP**. Yes, her campaign is now $200 million and 170,000 new volunteers richer.
**But the campaign now shifts** into a new phase, and itâs the next three weeks before the Democratic National Convention that will dictate whether Harris can harness the momentum, grow her appeal and potentially expand the electoral map in Democratsâ favor.
**None of those things are guaranteed,** as Harris herself is telling aides and allies, weâre told: âShe is not blinded by the sugar,â said one insider who recently spoke with Harris. âShe understands the gravity and excitement of the moment but also understands the work that needs to be done.â
**Foremost on her mind** is activating the new volunteers and getting them out knocking on doors. Harris and emerging campaign brain trust share the view that shifting the fundamentals of the race will be difficult with a calcified electorate and fragmented media environment.
**But even some Republicans acknowledge** she has been handed a major opportunity to reset the race over the coming weeks.

metatags.fulltext: Irish singer Sinead OâConnorâs cause of death has been revealed to the public just one year after her passing at 56. According to the New York Post, the Grammy winner died from both asthma and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (COPD). Her husband, John Reynolds, registered her death as such in London this week. According to the outlet, a respiratory tract infection that OâConnor had at the time of her death was also a contributing factor. Before the official report, the singer was reported to have died of natural causes after being found âunresponsiveâ in her London apartment. In January 2022, OâConnor lost her second youngest son, Shane Lunny, after he died by suicide. According to People, OâConnor took to Twitter, now X, to mourn his passing in a since-deleted message. âMy beautiful son, Nevi'im Nesta Ali Shane O'Connor, the very light of my life, decided to end his earthly struggle today and is now with God," she wrote. #### Tom Williams/CQ-Roll Call, Inc via Getty Images
The Republican mayor of the third-largest city in Arizona came out in support of Vice President Kamala Harris on Monday, calling in an op-ed in the _Arizona Republic_ for his fellow conservatives to join him in backing her for president. Mesa Mayor John Giles invoked the late Sen. John McCain and his motto of âCountry Firstâ in making the case for Harris, saying that Republicans have âa moral and ethical responsibilityâ to choose country over party come November. Hailing Harrisâ candidacy as a return to political âdecency,â the mayor also praised her and President Joe Biden for their work investing in the battleground stateâs economy, saying the pair âare delivering thousands of new jobs to Arizonans and helping us grow critical industries.â Giles, who has been mayor of Mesa since 2014, also took the opportunity to slam former President Donald Trump, saying he represents a âthreat to democracy.â Ticking off the points against Trump, including his attempts to overturn the results of the 2020 election, Giles noted that the former president has done little to support the Grand Canyon State, preferring to exploit its immigration and border crises for âpersonal political gain.â
